<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,263,685]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,210,264,290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[220,368,263,290]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloi">
<emphasis box="[220,368,263,290]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Cassia selloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on the collection 
<emphasis box="[828,952,263,289]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Sellow s.n.</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1028,1099,263,289]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, without any indication of the herbarium where the type was deposited. 
<bibRefCitation author="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C." box="[589,858,299,326]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" pagination="1 - 454" refId="ref5268" refString="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C. (1982) The American Cassiinae: A synoptical revision of Leguminosae tribe Cassieae subtribe Cassiinae in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 35: 1 - 454." type="journal article" year="1982">Irwin &amp; Barneby (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, in their revision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[1073,1141,300,326]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1073,1141,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Senna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggested a specimen from Lambert’s personal herbarium as the 
<typeStatus box="[550,648,335,361]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[685,785,335,362]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
<taxonomicName box="[685,781,335,362]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloi">C. selloi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, H. H." box="[950,1103,335,362]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" pagination="489 - 553" refId="ref5500" refString="Miller, H. H. (1970) The herbarium of Aylmer Bourke Lambert notes on its acquisition, dispersal, and present whereabouts. Taxon 19: 489 - 553. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1218947" type="journal article" year="1970">Miller (1970)</bibRefCitation>
, George Don described several new species from the Lambert Herbarium, and after Lambert’s death, the collection was divided into approximately 317 lots, which are now deposited in at least 18 different institutions in Europe and the 
<collectingCountry box="[1115,1268,407,434]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">United States</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,263,685]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="HAL" country="Brazil" county="We" location="Sellow" municipality="Wien Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
Our research found 
<specimenCount box="[409,564,443,469]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
referring to the collection 
<emphasis box="[857,969,443,469]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFC859FC8FC5E03A4" box="[857,932,443,469]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Sellow" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Sellow</location>
s.n
</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1035,1103,443,469]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Brazil</collectingCountry>
deposited in different herbaria: 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFF549FACFE32038B" box="[136,456,479,506]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Herbarium of Field Museum" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Herbarium of Field Museum</location>
(F, barcodes V0057681F and V0093913F), 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFC699FACFBD40388" box="[949,1070,479,505]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Herbarium</location>
Martin-Luther-Universität (
<collectionCode box="[1385,1447,480,506]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15866" name="Martin-Luther-Universität" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" type="Herbarium">HAL</collectionCode>
, barcode HAL0120725), 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFE7F9C70FDE6006C" box="[419,540,515,541]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Herbarium</location>
of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFDAB9C70FC1C006F" box="[631,998,515,542]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Royal Botanic Gardens of Kew" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Royal Botanic Gardens of Kew</location>
(K, barcode K000555409), 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFAEE9C70FD8A0030" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Herbarium of Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Herbarium of Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle</location>
(P, barcode P00798381), and 
<collectingMunicipality box="[990,1184,551,577]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Wien Herbarium</collectingMunicipality>
(W-0028642). 
<collectingCounty box="[1367,1404,552,578]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">We</collectingCounty>
are designating here the specimen deposited at P under barcode P00798381 as the 
<typeStatus box="[1029,1135,587,613]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">lectotype</typeStatus>
, as it is well preserved with leaves and flowers (characters used in the protologue), and has label annotations that coincide with those of the original description
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
